    "id": "usd_swaption_normal_vol",
    "description": "USD swaption normal-vol surface calibrated against a 3×3 (expiry × tenor) grid of SwaptionVol quotes, layered on discount and forward curves in initial_market. Demonstrates the standard rates-vol analyst workflow: given a pre-existing USD-OIS discount curve and USD-SOFR-3M forward curve, fit per-bucket SABR (β=0) parameters to normal vols quoted in basis points. The produced VolCube is keyed as 'USD-SWAPTION-NORMAL-VOL' and is retrievable via MarketContext::get_vol_provider(). Note: swaption_vol calibration produces a VolCube (not a VolSurface), so the accessor is get_vol_provider rather than get_surface. The grid uses 3 expiries (1y, 2y, 5y from base 2026-05-08) × 3 swap tenors (2y, 5y, 10y) × 3 strikes (ATM-50bp, ATM, ATM+50bp) for a total of 27 quotes. Normal vols range from 55–80 bp, representative of a 5% rate environment. Used as a prerequisite for a full rates-vol composite envelope.",
